I"o<p>When one is tasked with <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/fleeting-note-persisting-resembles-memory-consolidation">tediously consolidating fleeting notes into robust notes</a>, the consumption-creation ratio becomes particularly salient. By adding friction to consumption (i.e. by forcing this <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-contents-resemble-long-term-memory">elaboration contraint</a>), the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/creative-output-can-support-educational-input-in-free-learning">free learner</a> is nudged towards creation, rather than mindless consumption.</p>
